    {
      "id": "f1e49c90_f631a3c4",
      "file_path": "policy-endpoints/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/endpoints/http/server/internal/JettyJerseyServer.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 190,
      "message": "Can a DefaultServlet be in the same package as a JaxRs Servlet? \nNo, static resources handled by\nDefaultServlet are not source code, they could be existed at src/main/resources, or stand alone folder like /project/webapp.\n\ncan a JaxRs Servlet and the DefaultServlet coexist under the same \"servletPath\"? \nNo, they can't, otherwise IllegalStateException would happpen. \nI also use jerseyServlets and defaultServlets to store two types of servlets.",
